The paper investigates the performance of artificial neurons in recurrent neural networks (RNNs) trained with maximum likelihood. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the extraction of additional information that is not relevant for predicting the future, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve datasets related to motion and sketches, which could fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
